record_data.record_title: Provision of Emergency Power - Arapahoe Facility
record_data.record_plain_text:
Seller will provide real power produced by its Arapahoe natural gas-filed generating facility (the "Arapahoe Facility") pursuant to its obligations under the Amended and Restated Generation Interconnection Agreement between Public Service Company of Colorado and Black Hills Colorado, LLC, n/k/a SWG Colorado, LLC, or the successor to said agreement or agreements, at a price determined through the following pricing mechanism:
Price = (Price per MWH * MWH) + Startup Charges
Where:
Price per MWH = [(price of natural gas delivered to Arapahoe Facility in connection with power production) + Balancing Fees) * Heat Rate] + VOM
Balancing Fees = any balancing fees or imbalance charges associated with delivery of natural gas to Fountain Valley Facility
VOM = Variable operating and maintenance costs associated with power production
Startup Charges = fixed charge of $14,600 per start per turbine
All such sales of electric capacity or energy at wholesale shall be pursuant to Seller's market-based rate wholesale power sales tariff on file with FERC.
